+System Context: I am working on an unsupervised community detection pipeline. Stage 1 utilizes multiple runs of Louvain/Leiden to generate structural community priors. Stage 2 uses a Graph Convolutional Network (GCN) to fuse node attributes (X) and graph topology (A) to generate a node embedding matrix (H). Stage 3 uses these embeddings and the priors to perform a soft-assignment clustering via a dot-product similarity and Softmax. Objective: Update the GCN model class in my codebase to include Layer Normalization (nn.LayerNorm). This is required to stabilize the feature variance before the activation function and prevent the Adam optimizer from struggling with exploding/vanishing gradients caused by hub nodes. Strict Architectural Directives: 1. Location: The LayerNorm must be applied immediately after the graph convolution (matrix multiplication) and immediately before the activation function (ReLU/Leaky ReLU). 2. Dimension Targeting: The LayerNorm should normalize across the feature dimension of the nodes. For a hidden layer outputting hidden_dim features, initialize it as nn.LayerNorm(hidden_dim). 3. Preserve L2 Normalization: My network relies on L2 Normalization at the absolute end of the forward pass to project the final embeddings onto a unit hypersphere for Stage 3 cosine similarity. Do not remove or alter the final F.normalize(x, p=2, dim=1) step. LayerNorm does not replace L2 Normalization; they serve completely different geometric purposes. Expected Transformation: Change the current logic pattern from [x = self.gc1(x, adj) then x = F.leaky_relu(x)] to the target logic pattern [x = self.gc1(x, adj) then x = self.layer_norm1(x) then x = F.leaky_relu(x)]. Action Required: 1. Locate my GCN model class. 2. Add the appropriate nn.LayerNorm initializations in the __init__ method. 3. Update the forward pass to reflect the target logic pattern above. 4. Review the final layer to ensure the spherical L2 Normalization remains perfectly intact. Please output the refactored GCN class and briefly explain the changes you made. Name the final ouput file from the main file "LayerNorm.csv"

